description: From the participle stem of Latin compenetro.

verbs.description: compenetrate (third-person singular simple present compenetrates, present participle compenetrating, simple past and past participle compenetrated)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To penetrate every part of; to permeate.
examples: In this [state] the Deity compenetrates the soul, but in such a hidden way that the soul [... etc.]

entries.meaning: To penetrate mutually or reciprocally; to interpenetrate.
